    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen running Neovim with the `--embed` flag, if it is placed *after* any file arguments, then an empty buffer will be opened alongside the file(s) listed.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nThis (potential) bug was discovered with Neovide, which [recently changed how `--embed` is attached to the Neovim arguments](https://github.com/neovide/neovide/commit/4b8d6f3423bdbe2a922cf00dd2406fde52fc9137). Neovide will [not append `--embed` if it is present in the supplied arguments to Neovim](https://github.com/neovide/neovide/blob/main/src/bridge/command.rs#L129), making this easy to test.\n\nUsing Neovide as the frontend, in a directory with `init.lua`:\n1) Run:\n    ```sh\n    neovide --no-tabs -- --embed init.lua # Generated command: nvim --embed init.lua\n    ```\n    Above opens `init.lua` as it would be in the TUI.\n2) Run:\n    ```sh\n    neovide --no-tabs -- init.lua --embed  # Generated command (also without manual --embed): nvim init.lua  --embed\n    ```\n    Above opens an empty buffer, then `init.lua`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe output of 1) above is correct, and 2) should match it.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.1, 0.11.6\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 25.11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nN/A\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage, Nix",
