            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Hmm, `edit_stdin()` is called in the middle of argument parsing to determine whether there can be a potential stdin to read from:\n```c\n      int alist_fnum_flag = edit_stdin(parmp)\n                            ? 1   // add buffer nr after exp.\n                            : 2;  // add buffer number now and use curbuf\n      alist_add(&global_alist, p, alist_fnum_flag);\n```\nThis doesn't look right to me, but I'm not sure how to change it, or if changing it will break things.",
