            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I successfully reproduce the problem, however i got stuck at building debug-environment. I firstly try to use rr to record `neovide --no-tabs -- --embed init.lua` but rr and neovide incompatible in my desktop-environment and i have no idea how to fix it.\n\nThen i use rr record `nvim --embed test.txt ` directly, but of course it need ui-attach, it sleep in `remote_ui_wait_for_attach` and at this point, i check the buffer_list in curbuf and firstbuf and it seem right. So i suspect that execution flow is incomplete, but idk how to builld a debug environment properly. So i am here ask for some advice, would it be acceptable to simulate the UI connection using a minimal Python (pynvim) or Lua script?",
