            "body": "Thank you! Now i see, `edit_stdin` rely on three global variable `headless_mode embedded_mode stdin_isatty` . When parsing command like this `cat | nvim filename --embed ` ,  at the time we parsing the argument `filename`, the `embedded_mode` is not be set, and the `stdin_isatty` equals True, so `edit_stdin(parmp)` equals True and we dont reuse the `curbuf`.\n\nA solution maybe delay the `alist_add` ? or just pre-scan the args that set the flags like `--embed --headless...` ?  I dont know if i have leave the same comment here, and be deleted, if so, i am so sorry for that",
